deck: Main protagonist of Guilty Gear. Being the first of a new kind, the Prototype Gear, he's now a bounty hunter with a sense of honor, in search of other Gears that threaten the world and everyone living in it. He also has business to settle with the main antagonist, only know as That Man.
description:
Sol Badguy - known previously as Frederick - was previously a man who was working on a project known as the Gear Project. Not only he was a lead scientist on that project, but he also ended up being the Prototype Gear. Because of the longetivity known to Gears, Frederick ended up living for 100 hundred years prior to the Guilty Gear games' events and beyond.

During that time, he destroyed several Gear facilities; in protest of the resurgence of the Gear Project, he managed to build the Outrage - which is composed of eight weapons separated from each other, being that Sol has one on his possession (Fireseal, also named Fuuenken); he also saved Kliff Undersn (one of the leaders of the Holy Order and the one who named Ky Kiske leader of the Holy Knights) when Kliff was still a young boy. He would later encounter the Nightwalker, Slayer, who would bestow upon him the name "Sol" and would act as a mentor of sorts. Roughly half a century later, he was himself recruited into the Order, as a bounty hunter named "Sol Badguy". Sol took part in the Crusades, ironically becoming one of the best fighters on the human side. At this time, he was a member of the Sacred Order of Holy Knights (Seikishidan). He acquired the nickname "Corrupted [or Immoral] Flame" (Haitoku no Honoo) during that time, a name that such figures as I-No and Justice use for him later. However, he later became disenchanted with the methods of the Sacred Order. At an unspecified time, Sol fled the order, taking with him the Fuuenken, which the Holy Knights had come to consider a sacred treasure the theft earned him Ky Kiske's enmity. Ironically, Sol himself forged the Fuuenken.
name: Sol Badguy

deck: One time succesfull actor who fell on hard times. He became a stage actor in WWII.
description:
Origin

Arthur Bombridge was a succesfull actor in Hollywood, known as Cowboy Artie to his fans. As a human being, he was an asshole. He was very short, but the magic of Hollywood made him a large man on screen. After he was photographed by a paparazzi when he was in the pool seducing a young starlet, he fell from grace.

Arthur moved to France just as WWII broke out in Europe. To give himself some credence, he legally changed his first name to 'Sir'. He became a stage actor in Paris, making fun of Hitler. It was there that he met Sergeant Nicolas Highroad, who immediatly became his biggest fan.

Nicolas wanted to buy Arthur a drink. The brothel Arthur took the naive Nicolas to, was overrun by the Brotherhood of the Iron Cross who were about to kidnap Hitler's ex-lover Sloan Applebee. Chivalrous as he is, Nicolas rescued Sloan, helped by the handy Arthur. This set them on the adventure to retrieve a precious jewel and stop Hitler from bombing the North Pole so the ice would met and overflow the world. They do so with the help of failed kamikaze pilot Commander Ki and later retreat to an unknown island in the British West Indies where they grew old together.
name: Arthur Bombridge III

deck: Former lover of Adolf Hitler, she helped stop Hitler's plans and win World War II.
description:
Origin

Sloan Applebee is the widow of RAF Captain Kenneth Applebee who crashed over Germany in WWII. She somehow ended up as Hitler's lover, all the while trying to get to his plans. On the day Hitler tired of her and sent her out on the street, she had stolen one of his plans. Broke, she ended up as a prostitute in Madame Eugena's brothel, where Hitler's ninja group, the Brotherhood of the Iron Cross, found her and tried to kidnap her. This was stopped by American sergeant Nicolas Highroad and failed Hollywood actor Arthur Bombridge III. This set them on the adventure to retrieve a precious jewel and stop Hitler from bombing the North Pole so the ice would met and overflow the world. They do so with the help of failed kamikaze pilot Commander Ki and later retreat to an unknown island in the British West Indies where they grew old together.
name: Sloan Applebee

deck: Naive but brave American sergeant who helped win World War II.
description:
Origin

After seeing a show by Arthur Bombridge III, the American sergeant Nicolas Highroad became Arthur's biggest fan and wanted to buy Arthur a drink. Arriving in the brothel, Nicolas saw his comrades killed and Sloan Applebee about to be kidnapped by the Brotherhood of the Iron Cross. Chivalrous as he is, Nicolas rescued Sloan, helped by the handy Arthur. This set them on the adventure to retrieve a precious jewel and stop Hitler from bombing the North Pole so the ice would met and overflow the world. They do so with the help of failed kamikaze pilot Commander Ki and later retreat to an unknown island in the British West Indies where they grew old together.
name: Nicolas Highroad

deck: Failed kamikaze pilot who later helped the allies win World War II.
description:
Origin

Trained as a kamikaze pilot, Ki wasn't ultimately able to commit suicide by crashing his plane. He pulled up at the last second. Considering himself a failure, he went to France and became a drunk. He was discovered by Sergeant Nicolas Highroad, Arthur Bombridge III and Sloan Applebee. They needed a pilot to get to the North Pole retrieve a precious jewel and to stop Hitler from setting off bombs there which would melt the ice and overflow the world. They did so and later retreated to an unknown island in the British West Indies where they grew old together.
name: Commander Ki
